Father's Day takes place on Sunday June 19 the year, and there is arguably no better way to spend it than by sharing some traditional 'Dad jokes' with the man in your life. Whether your father figure is a jokester himself, or need to brush up on his funny one-liners, Express.co.uk has compiled some of the best to get your Dad laughing his socks off today. Nothing makes a Dad joke quite like a punch line. Oftentimes, punchline jokes are so bad they are good. Here are a few punch line jokes to get a giggle out of your Dad, Grandad, step-dad or any other father figure in your life. READ MORE: 'That hurt!' David Tennant's wife Georgia on surviving cancer 1. Why are balloons so expensive? Inflation. 2. What do you call cheese that isn’t yours? Nacho cheese! 3. Why can’t you send a duck to space? Because the bill would be astronomical. DON'T MISSSophie Wessex turns heads in £1,250 aquamarine necklace and £4k dress [PICTURES]Dating after divorce: How to build the perfect dating app profile [EXPLAINER]Festival essentials checklist: Key camping items not to forget [INSIGHT] 4. What side of a tree grows the most branches? The outside! 5. What do you call a monkey in a minefield? A baboom! 6. Why is Peter Pan always flying? Because he Neverlands. 7. Why did the broom decide to go to bed? It was very sweepy. 8. What do you call an illegally parked frog? Toad. One-liners are great because you don't even need a willing participant. Instead, get some unexpected laughs out of your audience with these humorous one-liners.